{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #889: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. For $k\\geq 0$ and $n\\geq 1$ let $v(n,k)$ count the prime factors of $n+k$ which do not divide $n+i$ for $0\\leq i<k$. Equivalently, $v(n,k)$ counts the number of prime factors of $n+k$ which are $>k$.\n\nIs it true that\\[v_0(n)=\\max_{k\\geq 0}v(n,k)\\to \\infty\\]as $n\\to \\infty$? Current best: A question of Erd\\H{o}s and Selfridge \\cite{ErSe67}, who could only show that $v_0(n)\\geq 2$ for $n\\geq 17$. More generally, they conjecture that\\[v_l(n)=\\max_{k\\geq l}v(n,k)\\to \\infty\\]as $n\\to \\infty$, for every fixed $l$, but could not even prove that $v_1(n)\\geq 2$ for all large $n$. Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_12af8d1ecdea9af4","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos889.erdos_889 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos889.erdos_889.","id":"vf_41b749a068054cde","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/889.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_12af8d1ecdea9af4","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:889","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_41b749a068054cde","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:889","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_41b749a068054cde","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9